WEBVTT

00:08.312 --> 00:09.444
- When I was a boy,
I had an uncle

00:09.487 --> 00:11.011
who traveled all over Asia,

00:11.054 --> 00:14.666
and he would write me
beautiful letters

00:14.710 --> 00:16.277
talking about his adventures.

00:16.320 --> 00:18.627
- Now all we get in the mail
are bills

00:18.670 --> 00:20.281
and credit card rip-offs.

00:20.324 --> 00:22.631
[laughter]

00:22.674 --> 00:25.808
- Instead of letters to express
our deepest feelings,

00:25.851 --> 00:30.508
[scoffs] they gave us emails,
texts, tweets,

00:30.552 --> 00:32.641
the fast-foods
of human communication.

00:32.684 --> 00:34.773
Fact: The brains of children

00:34.817 --> 00:36.645
that surf the net
for seven hours a day

00:36.688 --> 00:38.473
literally shrink in the areas

00:38.516 --> 00:40.997
where they develop
compassion and empathy.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.216
- Wow.

00:42.259 --> 00:44.914
- But not where they develop
bad posture.

00:44.957 --> 00:46.350
[laughter]

00:46.394 --> 00:48.352
- I'm proud of all of you.

00:48.396 --> 00:51.964
You are all the leaders
and the teachers now.

00:52.008 --> 00:54.967
You had the courage
to break tech addiction

00:55.011 --> 00:56.491
and free your minds.

00:56.534 --> 00:59.537
[inspiring music]

00:59.581 --> 01:01.496
- Let's put 'em down
over here.

01:01.539 --> 01:03.846
- Wait up, wait up!
[indistinct chatter]

01:03.889 --> 01:05.543
- Make sure
that header's level.

01:05.587 --> 01:08.590
Daisy, will you refill
our thermos please?

01:08.633 --> 01:10.983
[children laughing]

01:11.027 --> 01:13.073
It's coming along.
- Thanks, Uncle Quentin.

01:13.116 --> 01:15.249
We should have it done
before the first snow.

01:15.292 --> 01:16.685
- Too fast!

01:16.728 --> 01:19.079
- Ray.
John.

01:20.384 --> 01:22.473
- Mom!
[chatter]

01:23.735 --> 01:25.781
- I have another task
for you.

01:25.824 --> 01:28.697
One that I would only trust
to my most loyal friends.

01:28.740 --> 01:32.353
I had a disturbing dream
last night.

01:32.396 --> 01:35.225
A revelation.

01:35.269 --> 01:37.619
A fox feasting on her young.

01:37.662 --> 01:40.100
- What do you think it means?

01:40.143 --> 01:42.537
- That there is an obstacle
to our progress.

01:42.580 --> 01:44.887
[ominous music]

01:44.930 --> 01:46.976
An obstacle
that needs to be removed.

01:47.019 --> 01:48.586
♪

01:48.630 --> 01:50.110
[baby cooing]

01:50.153 --> 01:52.547
- Oh, look at those
big brown eyes.

01:52.590 --> 01:55.376
Aren't you a cutie pie?

01:55.419 --> 01:57.204
You're one of the moms
from the Meadow?

01:57.247 --> 01:58.466
- Uh, yes, ma'am.

01:58.509 --> 02:00.207
- Disposables?

02:00.250 --> 02:02.209
- Uh, it's for, uh, Jade.

02:02.252 --> 02:03.384
- Hmm.
- Yeah.

02:03.427 --> 02:05.212
- Can I use your phone?

02:05.255 --> 02:07.736
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

02:07.779 --> 02:09.172
- One of these days
they're gonna let us

02:09.216 --> 02:11.696
put up some cell towers
around here.

02:11.740 --> 02:13.133
- In the Quiet Zone?
[chuckles]

02:13.176 --> 02:15.309
Don't hold your breath,
young lady.

02:15.352 --> 02:17.354
- [sighs]
[phone beeps]

02:17.398 --> 02:20.531
[tense music]

02:20.575 --> 02:23.447
♪

02:23.491 --> 02:25.275
- Thank you.
- Everything okay, Rose?

02:25.319 --> 02:27.234
- Uh, yeah, sure.

02:27.277 --> 02:29.410
- Oh, okay.
- Mm-hmm.

02:29.453 --> 02:31.629
- Look, it's your mama.

02:31.673 --> 02:33.370
- Hi.
Hey, Marco told us a joke.

02:33.414 --> 02:34.632
Go ahead Marco.

02:34.676 --> 02:36.199
- What did the ocean
say to the beach?

02:36.243 --> 02:37.331
- I don't know, Marco.

02:37.374 --> 02:38.506
What did the ocean
say to the beach?

02:38.549 --> 02:40.334
- Nothing.
It just waved.

02:40.377 --> 02:42.945
- [laughs]
All right, come on.

02:42.988 --> 02:45.165
- I got her.

02:45.208 --> 02:47.428
- Rose.

02:47.471 --> 02:49.256
Quentin needs to talk to you.

02:49.299 --> 02:51.954
- Uh, we're--we're on our way
back to the Meadow.

02:51.997 --> 02:54.261
Is something wrong?
- No big deal.

02:54.304 --> 02:56.828
John and me will go back
with you and the kids.

02:56.872 --> 02:59.570
Billy, you and Leanne
drive back to the Meadow.

02:59.614 --> 03:06.621
♪

03:10.494 --> 03:12.844
[engine starts]

03:22.114 --> 03:26.902
- ♪ La, da, da, da,
la, da, da, dum ♪

03:26.945 --> 03:30.253
♪ La, da, da, da

03:30.297 --> 03:35.258
♪ La, da, da, da, da, da

03:35.302 --> 03:37.260
- [crying]

03:37.304 --> 03:39.306
- Oh!

03:39.349 --> 03:41.786
♪

03:41.830 --> 03:44.267
Oh, my God.
Rose!

03:44.311 --> 03:46.443
Rose!
- My babies--

03:46.487 --> 03:49.011
- Rose!
- My babies--

03:49.054 --> 03:52.275
They killed my babies.
[cries]

03:52.319 --> 03:54.190
They killed my babies!

04:01.893 --> 04:03.895
- Mr. Riley's putting
the antenna

04:03.939 --> 04:05.680
on the roof
of the school today.

04:05.723 --> 04:08.030
We have a super powerful
transceiver

04:08.073 --> 04:09.727
that reaches
all the way to Australia.

04:09.771 --> 04:12.382
- Wow, that sounds very cool.

04:12.426 --> 04:15.342
Look what I found last night.

04:15.385 --> 04:17.213
It's your mom's old compass.

04:17.257 --> 04:20.172
I signed us up for
an orienteering competition.

04:21.609 --> 04:23.611
- That's something
I did with mom.

04:25.177 --> 04:27.441
- I know. You guys were
a pretty good team.

04:27.484 --> 04:29.617
I thought we might be
a pretty good team too.

04:29.660 --> 04:31.358
- Well, I gotta get ready
for school.

04:33.621 --> 04:36.580
[dramatic music]

04:36.624 --> 04:37.799
- [sighs]

04:37.842 --> 04:39.714
♪

04:39.757 --> 04:42.282
[sighs]

04:42.325 --> 04:44.327
I messed up, didn't I?

04:44.371 --> 04:46.329
- Mmm.
Not yet.

04:46.373 --> 04:49.767
Ask Clint about Happy.
- Who's Happy?

04:49.811 --> 04:53.293
- Dog Angelyne had
when she was a kid.

04:54.163 --> 04:57.253
- [sighs]
[phone buzzing]

05:00.343 --> 05:03.085
- Quentin Garvey, Ray Bell,
and John Truro,

05:03.128 --> 05:05.174
on the run for
the murders of three children

05:05.217 --> 05:08.003
and attempted murder of Nellie
Rose Manning, their mother.

05:08.046 --> 05:10.135
She's in ICU, under sedation.

05:10.179 --> 05:11.920
Garvey is the leader
of the Meadow,

05:11.963 --> 05:14.096
an anti-tech commune
outside of Malone.

05:14.139 --> 05:16.185
- Spitting distance
from Canada.

05:16.228 --> 05:18.709
It's also in the middle
of a National Radio Quiet Zone,

05:18.753 --> 05:20.015
where radio, Wi-Fi,

05:20.058 --> 05:21.669
and cellular transmissions
are restricted.

05:21.712 --> 05:23.801
Perfect for the Meadow's
anti-tech lifestyle.

05:23.845 --> 05:25.368
- Man's living
in the Stone Ages.

05:25.412 --> 05:27.327
- Victims were found
in the woods near the commune.

05:27.370 --> 05:30.025
Kids were killed with
a single gunshot to the chest.

05:30.068 --> 05:33.028
Canadian cops are on a alert.
- And Garvey's background?

05:33.071 --> 05:35.465
- Land fraud in North Carolina.
He served eight years.

05:35.509 --> 05:38.163
- From con man to cult leader.
That's a short leap.

05:38.207 --> 05:39.774
- He started the Meadow
five years ago

05:39.817 --> 05:41.210
and convinced 40 people

05:41.253 --> 05:43.038
to take a step back
into the Analog Age with him.

05:43.952 --> 05:46.476
- Nellie Rose, what's her role?

05:46.520 --> 05:49.697
- She's Garvey's wife.
The three kids were his.

05:49.740 --> 05:52.656
- He killed his own kids?
Oh, man.

05:52.700 --> 05:54.179
- He's a con man.

05:54.223 --> 05:56.399
Most likely he convinced
his two apostles to do it.

05:56.443 --> 05:59.533
A little charisma and some
fancy sounding dogma

05:59.576 --> 06:02.187
can convince people to do
the worst atrocities.

06:03.841 --> 06:06.191
- I just can't get it
out of my head.

06:06.235 --> 06:09.630
Her coming out of the woods
with that baby in her arms.

06:09.673 --> 06:12.241
- You told police she was in
your store earlier that day?

06:12.284 --> 06:13.721
- With a baby.

06:13.764 --> 06:17.768
Rose's sister Leanne was
outside with this boy, Billy,

06:17.812 --> 06:19.988
keeping an eye
on the other little ones.

06:20.031 --> 06:22.338
- How did Rose seem?
- Fidgety.

06:22.382 --> 06:24.253
She bought some snacks
and diapers,

06:24.296 --> 06:26.560
and she asked to use our phone.

06:26.603 --> 06:29.214
- Can I take a look?

06:29.258 --> 06:32.000
- What about Quentin Garvey
and these two?

06:32.043 --> 06:33.436
You ever talk to them?

06:33.480 --> 06:36.570
- Oh, these other two
I've seen waiting outside

06:36.613 --> 06:39.790
while the "wives," as they
call them, do the shopping.

06:39.834 --> 06:41.052
- As they call them?

06:41.096 --> 06:42.532
You don't believe
they were married?

06:42.576 --> 06:44.665
- Not unless they changed
the laws against polygamy.

06:44.708 --> 06:46.188
- The men have
more than one mate?

06:46.231 --> 06:47.755
- That's what I understand.

06:47.798 --> 06:50.235
Quentin himself
had a second wife--Iris.

06:50.279 --> 06:51.628
Younger than Rose.

06:51.672 --> 06:53.543
- Younger women
for older dudes.

06:53.587 --> 06:54.849
Garvey's latest con.

06:54.892 --> 06:56.328
- And you said Rose
was fidgety.

06:56.372 --> 06:58.896
Did she say or do
anything unusual?

07:00.420 --> 07:02.160
- The diapers.

07:02.204 --> 07:04.859
These people
never buy disposables.

07:04.902 --> 07:06.600
They use cloth ones.

07:06.643 --> 07:08.428
- Here you go.
Thank you.

07:08.471 --> 07:10.212
- Thanks for your help.
Appreciate it.

07:10.255 --> 07:11.474
- Thank you.

07:11.518 --> 07:13.433
[investigative music]

07:13.476 --> 07:15.783
- She made a call to
her mother, Sheilah Manning,

07:15.826 --> 07:17.219
in Keene, New Hampshire.

07:17.262 --> 07:19.917
- A call home,
disposable diapers, snacks--

07:19.961 --> 07:21.266
sounds like a road trip.

07:21.310 --> 07:24.226
- She called from here,
not from the Meadow.

07:24.269 --> 07:26.837
Garvey wasn't supposed to know.

07:26.881 --> 07:28.665
- Hey, hey!

07:28.709 --> 07:30.450
You have no right
to snoop around.

07:30.493 --> 07:31.929
This is our home!

07:31.973 --> 07:33.540
- If you tell us
where Quentin went, Iris,

07:33.583 --> 07:35.193
we won't have to snoop around.

07:35.237 --> 07:36.499
- I don't know.
He just left.

07:36.543 --> 07:37.848
- Oh, he didn't tell you?

07:37.892 --> 07:40.242
You're his wife, aren't you?
At least one of them.

07:40.285 --> 07:42.374
- Don't ridicule
what you don't understand.

07:42.418 --> 07:45.465
Quentin is a prophet
of the post-digital age.

07:45.508 --> 07:46.509
- That may be,

07:46.553 --> 07:47.728
but three of his children
are dead,

07:47.771 --> 07:48.816
and he's nowhere to be found.

07:48.859 --> 07:50.818
- Soon as we heard
they found Rose,

07:50.861 --> 07:52.602
Quentin knew
the police would blame him.

07:52.646 --> 07:53.951
That's why he had to leave.

07:53.995 --> 07:55.866
- She can wait with the others.

07:55.910 --> 07:59.783
[tense music]

07:59.827 --> 08:02.438
- Hey.
Check this out.

08:02.482 --> 08:04.222
♪

08:04.266 --> 08:06.660
Garvey has the only landline
on the farm.

08:06.703 --> 08:08.618
Life's good for the prophet.

08:08.662 --> 08:10.838
- I see a mirror on the
ceiling, I call an Uber.

08:10.881 --> 08:14.319
- Hmm.
"Free minds, free hearts."

08:14.363 --> 08:16.757
- Words to live by.
- Maybe.

08:16.800 --> 08:18.454
Quentin placed it
above his head.

08:18.498 --> 08:19.847
First thing he sees
in the morning,

08:19.890 --> 08:21.152
last thing he sees at night.

08:21.196 --> 08:23.807
- Prophet, murderer,
and now painter.

08:23.851 --> 08:26.375
- He didn't paint it.

08:27.768 --> 08:30.335
It's signed M.W.

08:31.989 --> 08:34.035
- Hey, I found that kid Billy

08:34.078 --> 08:35.732
who was at the store
with Rose's children,

08:35.776 --> 08:37.081
but we can't find
her sister Leanne.

08:37.125 --> 08:39.910
Nobody's seen her.

08:40.868 --> 08:42.304
- I don't know where Leanne is.

08:42.347 --> 08:44.219
I've been working
in the cow shed.

08:44.262 --> 08:46.221
- You were with her the other
day at the country store.

08:46.264 --> 08:48.049
Is she your girlfriend?

08:49.050 --> 08:50.921
- She is, isn't she, Billy?

08:50.965 --> 08:52.488
- Yeah, okay.

08:52.532 --> 08:53.837
- And you don't know
where she is?

08:53.881 --> 08:55.360
- No.

08:56.623 --> 08:59.843
- We're worried about her
after what happened.

08:59.887 --> 09:02.367
We believe Rose was planning on
leaving the Meadow for good

09:02.411 --> 09:05.327
and taking her kids
and Leanne with her.

09:05.370 --> 09:06.807
Do you know anything
about that?

09:06.850 --> 09:08.025
- No.

09:08.069 --> 09:09.679
- Why'd you go to the store
with them?

09:09.723 --> 09:13.204
- Leanne asked me.
Uncle Quentin said it was okay.

09:13.248 --> 09:14.858
- You need permission
to leave the Meadow?

09:14.902 --> 09:16.817
- He's the founder,
it's just respectful.

09:16.860 --> 09:18.601
- You're loyal to him.
We get it.

09:18.645 --> 09:20.734
Can make you act
against your better judgment.

09:20.777 --> 09:22.170
Like with Leanne,

09:22.213 --> 09:23.519
you don't seem to be
too worried that she's missing.

09:23.563 --> 09:25.826
If it was my girl,
I'd be going crazy.

09:25.869 --> 09:28.219
- Come on, Billy.

09:28.263 --> 09:30.439
You know where she is,
don't you?

09:30.482 --> 09:33.268
[tense music]

09:33.311 --> 09:35.575
- What happened, Billy?

09:35.618 --> 09:38.403
♪

09:38.447 --> 09:42.582
- When Uncle Quentin,
Uncle Ray, and John left...

09:42.625 --> 09:44.714
♪

09:44.758 --> 09:47.978
Leanne and Daisy, Uncle Ray's
wife, left with them.

09:48.675 --> 09:50.633
I don't know why
they had to take her.

09:50.677 --> 09:53.854
We wanted to get married
if the elders approved.

09:53.897 --> 09:55.769
- Leanne didn't want
to go with them?

09:55.812 --> 09:57.640
- It's not a choice.

09:57.684 --> 09:59.250
If Uncle Quentin asks you
to do something,

09:59.294 --> 10:03.037
you do it out of love
and respect.

10:03.080 --> 10:07.302
[tense eerie music]

10:07.345 --> 10:10.827
- Uncle Ray was driving
and John was in the car too.

10:10.871 --> 10:13.003
Ray said that we should stop

10:13.047 --> 10:15.266
and let the kids
relieve themselves.

10:15.310 --> 10:17.704
So I walked into the woods
with the kids...

10:19.575 --> 10:22.796
And then I saw Ray and John
coming with guns.

10:23.492 --> 10:26.713
So I grabbed Jade and Ruby,
and I told Marco to run.

10:26.756 --> 10:29.498
Then I fell and I dropped Ruby.

10:29.541 --> 10:34.068
And I heard, uh, Marco and Ruby
screaming for me.

10:34.982 --> 10:37.158
That's the last thing
I remember.

10:37.201 --> 10:40.204
- We're so sorry, Rose.
- Her name is Nellie.

10:40.248 --> 10:42.816
Rose is the name
that monster gave her.

10:43.512 --> 10:46.602
- Oh, my God.
Wait, where is Leanne?

10:46.646 --> 10:48.648
- Quentin took her
when he escaped.

10:48.691 --> 10:50.562
- Oh, God.
No.

10:50.606 --> 10:52.260
[stuttering] No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

10:52.303 --> 10:53.827
- Isn't that why you tried
to leave the Meadow?

10:53.870 --> 10:55.219
Because of Leanne?

10:55.263 --> 10:57.308
- [sighs]
Yes.

10:57.352 --> 11:00.703
Quentin wanted to take her
for bonding.

11:01.835 --> 11:03.532
To be his wife.

11:03.575 --> 11:06.230
She's only 17.

11:06.274 --> 11:08.972
And Quentin promised me
when I brought her here

11:09.016 --> 11:10.582
that she wouldn't
have to take a husband.

11:10.626 --> 11:12.106
- I cannot believe

11:12.149 --> 11:14.064
that you dragged your sister
into this nightmare.

11:14.108 --> 11:15.718
- I'm sorry, Mom!

11:15.762 --> 11:18.503
[dramatic music]

11:18.547 --> 11:22.029
- Is it possible Leanne went
with Quentin willingly?

11:22.072 --> 11:24.031
- [sighs] She's, um--

11:24.074 --> 11:26.207
She's in love with Billy.

11:27.338 --> 11:28.470
- Did Quentin ever talk about

11:28.513 --> 11:30.559
another property
he might go to?

11:30.602 --> 11:31.952
- Yeah.

11:31.995 --> 11:35.869
I heard him talk about someday,
when we're ready,

11:35.912 --> 11:38.741
going to Rising Sun.

11:38.785 --> 11:40.656
♪

11:40.700 --> 11:43.050
He said it's more wonderful
than the Meadow.

11:45.139 --> 11:47.054
- Thank you.
That's very helpful.

11:47.097 --> 11:49.709
And we're very sorry
about your children.

11:52.450 --> 11:54.452
- Still amazes me
how smart people

11:54.496 --> 11:56.716
can lose themselves in a cult.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.239
- What amazes me--

11:58.282 --> 12:00.458
how she's still alive when
her children were shot dead.

12:03.287 --> 12:07.248
Doctor, what were Mrs.
Manning's injuries, exactly?

12:07.291 --> 12:09.467
- A blunt force trauma
to the back of her head,

12:09.511 --> 12:11.731
and a gunshot wound
that grazed her left forehead.

12:11.774 --> 12:13.733
- Hard to see how the shooter
missed killing her.

12:13.776 --> 12:15.082
- Couldn't you tell
which came first--

12:15.125 --> 12:17.084
the gunshot wound
or the blow to the head?

12:17.127 --> 12:18.694
- The blow to the back
of the head.

12:18.738 --> 12:20.478
[beeping]
Oh.

12:20.522 --> 12:22.611
Excuse me.
- Yeah.

12:24.961 --> 12:26.528
- I talked to ballistics.

12:26.571 --> 12:28.617
They say the kids were killed
with the same .38.

12:28.660 --> 12:31.446
But get this:
A nine millimeter shell casing

12:31.489 --> 12:34.057
was found a hundred yards away
where Rose was wounded.

12:34.101 --> 12:36.799
- Whoever shot her
didn't want to kill her.

12:36.843 --> 12:38.627
They hit her
over the back of the head,

12:38.670 --> 12:40.934
then shot her to make
it look like she was dead.

12:40.977 --> 12:42.239
- Uncle Ray or John.

12:42.283 --> 12:43.980
Go figure that one of them
has a conscious.

12:44.024 --> 12:46.591
- Whichever one it is,
maybe they can help us.

12:46.635 --> 12:48.942
We need to protect them
from Quentin.

12:48.985 --> 12:51.248
I'll have the hospital
put out a press release

12:51.292 --> 12:53.947
that Rose died without
regaining consciousness.

12:53.990 --> 12:57.864
That way Quentin'll think
his gunmen did their job.

12:57.907 --> 13:00.344
It'll be one prophecy
the prophet gets wrong.

13:00.388 --> 13:02.259
♪

13:08.570 --> 13:10.441
- Despite the tireless efforts
of Dr. Ko and the Trauma Team

13:10.485 --> 13:12.008
here
at Franklin County Hospital,

13:12.052 --> 13:14.532
Nellie Rose Manning
passed away last night

13:14.576 --> 13:16.273
without regaining
consciousness.

13:16.317 --> 13:18.928
She suffered a devastating
gunshot wound to the head.

13:20.669 --> 13:22.540
- The gag order's in place.
[sighs]

13:22.584 --> 13:25.152
Rose was moved to
a private medical facility

13:25.195 --> 13:26.675
and registered under
an assumed name.

13:26.718 --> 13:28.546
- That's one base covered.
What else?

13:28.590 --> 13:30.331
- We put a tap
on Rose's mother's phone

13:30.374 --> 13:31.985
in case there's a ransom demand
for Leanne,

13:32.028 --> 13:34.030
and we finally ID'd
the getaway vehicles--

13:34.074 --> 13:37.468
BOLOS out for a burgundy Ford
sedan and a gold Chevy minivan.

13:37.512 --> 13:39.122
- The team sitting
on the Meadow

13:39.166 --> 13:41.864
says Quentin's little band of
believers are happy as clams.

13:41.908 --> 13:44.736
Except now Iris,
his second wife, is in charge.

13:44.780 --> 13:46.042
- Of course.

13:46.086 --> 13:48.131
The prophet doesn't trust
the men to run things.

13:48.175 --> 13:50.177
Only someone he can control
will do.

13:50.220 --> 13:52.614
How are we doing finding that
other refuge, Rising Sun?

13:52.657 --> 13:54.398
- Nothing but a house
in New Orleans.

13:54.442 --> 13:55.573
I checked the court records

13:55.617 --> 13:57.097
from Garvey's real
estate fraud case.

13:57.140 --> 13:58.489
He really is a piece of crap.

13:58.533 --> 14:00.883
He cheated
12 African American families

14:00.927 --> 14:02.885
in North Carolina
out of their land

14:02.929 --> 14:04.713
because they couldn't prove
titles to home

14:04.756 --> 14:06.541
that had been in their family
for generations.

14:06.584 --> 14:08.021
When Garvey was convicted,

14:08.064 --> 14:10.414
he had to forfeit
all the land he stole.

14:10.458 --> 14:12.590
- All the land
the court knew about.

14:12.634 --> 14:14.418
Take another look.
See if they missed anything.

14:14.462 --> 14:16.899
[investigative music]

14:16.943 --> 14:18.858
- We'll stop to eat
in Virginia.

14:18.901 --> 14:23.123
[dark music]

14:23.166 --> 14:26.909
[sighs]
So tell me, Ray,

14:26.953 --> 14:28.780
how is it the two of
you managed to foul up

14:28.824 --> 14:30.870
the task I gave you?
- That's on John.

14:30.913 --> 14:33.350
I did the hard part.
I took care of the kids.

14:33.394 --> 14:34.656
- And if I ask him
why Rose is still alive,

14:34.699 --> 14:36.353
I imagine he'd blame you.

14:36.397 --> 14:37.746
[door chimes]

14:37.789 --> 14:39.835
- Had enough for three
and a charger.

14:39.879 --> 14:45.493
♪

14:45.536 --> 14:47.147
- These boxes are open.

14:47.190 --> 14:49.410
- Well, the lady said
she had to activate them.

14:51.673 --> 14:53.718
- Let's see what
they're saying about us.

14:58.941 --> 15:00.769
Well, damn.

15:01.857 --> 15:03.815
Looks like Rose died
in the hospital

15:03.859 --> 15:06.470
without regaining
consciousness.

15:07.515 --> 15:09.909
Looks like you two
did your jobs after all.

15:15.349 --> 15:17.568
- Happy?
You mean Angelyne's dog?

15:17.612 --> 15:19.048
- That's what Nelson told me.

15:19.092 --> 15:21.007
- Happy was her first dog.

15:21.050 --> 15:24.227
She loved that dog.
He died when she was 11.

15:24.271 --> 15:25.881
So dad bought her a new dog,

15:25.925 --> 15:27.187
but she didn't want
to play with it.

15:27.230 --> 15:28.710
She felt guilty,

15:28.753 --> 15:30.625
like playing with this dog
would be disloyal to Happy.

15:30.668 --> 15:32.496
- And what happened?

15:32.540 --> 15:35.108
- Well,
Dad had a talk with her,

15:35.151 --> 15:37.240
and she started playing
with the dog.

15:37.284 --> 15:38.981
- So what'd he tell her?

15:39.025 --> 15:41.984
- I don't know.
I didn't hear.

15:44.030 --> 15:45.640
- [scoffs]

15:45.683 --> 15:48.382
- Yay, calories!
Carbs.

15:48.425 --> 15:49.992
- Hey, boss, check this out.

15:50.036 --> 15:54.127
The tap on Rose's mom's phone
picked up a voicemail.

15:54.170 --> 15:57.173
- Hi, Mrs. Manning,
my name's John.

15:57.217 --> 15:59.610
I'm so sorry for your loss.

15:59.654 --> 16:01.438
I was friends with Rose.

16:01.482 --> 16:04.006
I tried not to hurt her,
I really did.

16:04.050 --> 16:05.573
Please forgive me.

16:05.616 --> 16:07.836
- So John's our man
with a conscious.

16:07.879 --> 16:09.620
Warn Mrs. Manning
not to respond to him.

16:09.664 --> 16:11.535
- And I got a hit
on the burner he used.

16:11.579 --> 16:13.581
Bought it this morning
in downstate New York.

16:13.624 --> 16:16.062
- Good stuff.
- Thank you.

16:17.628 --> 16:20.936
- He paid cash for three
prepaid smartphones.

16:20.980 --> 16:23.156
He activated them himself right
away so he could use them.

16:23.199 --> 16:24.374
- Hey, I saw a camera outside.

16:24.418 --> 16:25.549
Could I take a quick look
at the feed?

16:25.593 --> 16:26.594
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

16:26.637 --> 16:28.291
Thanks.
- Was anyone with him?

16:28.335 --> 16:29.466
- Nope.

16:29.510 --> 16:30.685
He checked something
on his phone,

16:30.728 --> 16:32.469
went to the beverage
aisle to make a call.

16:32.513 --> 16:35.211
- Okay, I'm getting something.
Above you.

16:35.255 --> 16:37.039
[suspenseful music]

16:37.083 --> 16:40.042
We got Leanne and Daisy
in the minivan,

16:40.086 --> 16:42.044
and that is our boy Quentin
at the wheel.

16:42.088 --> 16:44.568
- Keeping a close eye
on the ladies.

16:44.612 --> 16:47.093
Doesn't trust Ray or John.

16:47.136 --> 16:49.921
Did this customer say anything
about where he was going?

16:49.965 --> 16:51.532
- Well, he did ask
if the phones

16:51.575 --> 16:52.924
worked in North Carolina.

16:52.968 --> 16:54.665
♪

16:54.709 --> 16:56.624
- Where Quentin stole land
from those families.

16:56.667 --> 16:59.453
♪

16:59.496 --> 17:00.845
- [sighs]
Quentin Garvey

17:00.889 --> 17:04.066
got a third cousin of mine
to deed him all my land.

17:04.110 --> 17:05.894
Next thing,
a process server's telling me

17:05.937 --> 17:07.765
that I gotta quit the place.

17:07.809 --> 17:09.680
Hell if I'm gonna
move off the land

17:09.724 --> 17:12.509
that's been in my family
since the Civil War.

17:12.553 --> 17:16.470
My son's a lawyer,
so we made a new claim.

17:16.513 --> 17:20.343
It took a couple of years,
but we got all 50 acres back.

17:20.387 --> 17:21.953
- And Garvey got a 6x8 cell.

17:21.997 --> 17:25.653
- He messed with the wrong man.
- He certainly did.

17:25.696 --> 17:27.133
- You know anybody that didn't
get their land back

17:27.176 --> 17:28.569
from Garvey?

17:28.612 --> 17:30.919
- My friend Delvin Tepper.

17:30.962 --> 17:34.836
He lost 800 acres,
west side of the river.

17:34.879 --> 17:36.794
His title fell to a company

17:36.838 --> 17:39.058
that they couldn't connect
to Garvey.

17:39.101 --> 17:41.799
- Thank you, Mr. Shelton.
Appreciate the help.

17:43.975 --> 17:46.152
- Delvin Tepper's named
as grantor to a farm

17:46.195 --> 17:49.285
now owned by East Asheville
Holdings LLC

17:49.329 --> 17:52.506
and four other corporations.
- Garvey tied it up in knots.

17:52.549 --> 17:54.116
- A farm on the west side
of the river would

17:54.160 --> 17:56.771
catch a glimpse of
the rising sun, wouldn't it?

17:56.814 --> 17:59.078
Let's give Garvey
a proper welcome.

17:59.121 --> 18:01.993
[dark music]

18:02.037 --> 18:05.171
- We'll make Rising Sun
just after dark.

18:05.214 --> 18:08.130
- When things cool down, we'll
bring everyone from the Meadow,

18:08.174 --> 18:11.786
but right now,
we need to talk about money.

18:11.829 --> 18:13.614
- Do you know
where we're going?

18:13.657 --> 18:15.181
- No, he won't tell me.

18:15.224 --> 18:16.530
♪

18:16.573 --> 18:20.055
- John.
I don't want to.

18:20.099 --> 18:21.535
- I know.

18:21.578 --> 18:23.014
- Can you just drive away
right now?

18:23.058 --> 18:25.408
You can just drop me off
somewhere.

18:25.452 --> 18:27.062
Please.
- I can't.

18:27.106 --> 18:28.716
He took the keys.

18:28.759 --> 18:30.587
But just wait.

18:32.372 --> 18:34.113
I'll get you away.

18:35.418 --> 18:38.943
- How's Leanne holding up?
- She's quiet.

18:38.987 --> 18:41.424
Nervous about the bonding.

18:41.468 --> 18:43.426
- Reassure her, Daisy.

18:43.470 --> 18:47.778
When we're safe at Rising Sun,
we will have the ceremony.

18:48.779 --> 18:52.087
[phone chimes]

18:52.131 --> 18:54.785
[phone buzzes]

19:00.878 --> 19:03.664
- Boss, Rose's mother
texted John's burner

19:03.707 --> 19:05.100
asking about Leanne.

19:05.144 --> 19:07.233
- Can hardly blame her.
Any response from John?

19:07.276 --> 19:08.886
- No.

19:08.930 --> 19:11.150
- Probably means Quentin
has the burner phone now.

19:11.193 --> 19:13.978
He'll figure out John
isn't a team player anymore.

19:14.022 --> 19:16.459
- Silver minivan approaching
from the north.

19:16.503 --> 19:18.157
Can't ID the occupants.

19:18.200 --> 19:20.942
No second vehicle in sight.
- Copy that.

19:20.985 --> 19:23.423
All positions stand by.

19:23.466 --> 19:30.386
♪

19:37.872 --> 19:40.657
[tires screech]
[siren blares]

19:40.701 --> 19:42.355
- [gasps]

19:42.398 --> 19:44.792
- FBI!
Drop your weapon!

19:44.835 --> 19:46.707
- [groans]

19:46.750 --> 19:48.535
- Show me your hands!
Show me your hands!

19:48.578 --> 19:49.971
- I didn't shoot!
I didn't shoot!

19:50.014 --> 19:51.668
- Hands, hands, hands!
Hands up all the way!

19:51.712 --> 19:53.583
Get out.

19:53.627 --> 19:55.455
- [groans]
- Don't move!

19:55.498 --> 19:57.370
Stay down!
- Go for EMS.

19:57.413 --> 19:59.198
- Two secondary structures
in the back.

19:59.241 --> 20:00.286
We want to preserve
the integrity...

20:00.329 --> 20:02.201
- Let's run a sweep
of the interior!

20:02.244 --> 20:04.246
- Clear those residential
structures!

20:04.290 --> 20:05.987
- Topside over
on the south side.

20:06.030 --> 20:08.598
- Yeah, copy that.
- Hello, who's this?

20:08.642 --> 20:10.252
Hello?

20:10.296 --> 20:16.693
♪

20:17.564 --> 20:19.174
- It's probably Quentin.

20:19.218 --> 20:22.003
- He must've heard
the whole thing go sideways.

20:22.046 --> 20:25.267
- He sent these two
to see if it was safe.

20:25.311 --> 20:27.138
They were slaughtered
while he listened in.

20:27.182 --> 20:30.185
- He still has Leanne
and Daisy.

20:30.229 --> 20:32.405
Who knows what he might do
to them.

20:32.448 --> 20:35.408
[tense music]

20:35.451 --> 20:38.672
♪

20:38.715 --> 20:40.326
- They made it to Rising Sun.

20:40.369 --> 20:42.676
♪

20:42.719 --> 20:44.330
All's good.

20:44.373 --> 20:49.073
♪

20:55.776 --> 20:57.343
- Uncle Quentin
had a revelation.

20:57.386 --> 21:01.042
He said that Rose was gonna
run away and go to the police.

21:02.348 --> 21:03.958
And he gave us guns,

21:04.001 --> 21:09.311
told us to take her
in the woods and shoot her.

21:09.355 --> 21:10.834
And her kids too.

21:10.878 --> 21:13.054
- Why the children?

21:13.097 --> 21:14.708
- He said without their mother

21:14.751 --> 21:16.884
they wouldn't survive
in the world.

21:16.927 --> 21:18.755
When Uncle Quentin
says something,

21:18.799 --> 21:21.236
you don't ask questions.

21:21.280 --> 21:26.023
But when Uncle Ray shot
the boy, it's like I woke up.

21:26.067 --> 21:29.113
I couldn't go through with it.
I--

21:29.157 --> 21:31.115
I tried to make it look
like Rose was dead,

21:31.159 --> 21:33.379
so that Uncle Ray
wouldn't finish her off,

21:33.422 --> 21:37.470
but it was for nothing.
- You didn't kill Rose.

21:38.122 --> 21:40.429
We said that she was dead
to fool Quentin.

21:40.473 --> 21:43.650
- [crying]

21:43.693 --> 21:46.522
Thank God, I never meant
any harm to come to anybody.

21:46.566 --> 21:48.872
- When Quentin sent you
and Ray to Rising Sun,

21:48.916 --> 21:50.352
where was he going?

21:50.396 --> 21:53.529
- He said to get things ready
while he went for money.

21:55.052 --> 21:58.404
He was looking at back roads
to get to West Virginia.

21:58.447 --> 22:00.841
[dramatic music]

22:00.884 --> 22:03.800
- Okay, there was something
about West Virginia

22:03.844 --> 22:06.107
in Daisy Anderson's file.
Here.

22:06.150 --> 22:08.196
Given name Maya Anderson,

22:08.239 --> 22:11.417
father's in-house counsel for a
coal company in West Virginia.

22:11.460 --> 22:15.159
Lives outside Charleston.
- About 300 miles from here.

22:15.203 --> 22:18.859
- Fire up the bird.
Alert Charleston police.

22:18.902 --> 22:21.296
- What's the combination,
Daddy?

22:21.340 --> 22:23.167
- Maya, why are you
doing this to us?

22:23.211 --> 22:25.561
- My name is Daisy.
- Please, sweetie,

22:25.605 --> 22:27.302
we thanked God you weren't
killed last night

22:27.346 --> 22:28.695
in North Carolina.
- Shut up!

22:28.738 --> 22:31.306
- Mmm.
[cries]

22:31.350 --> 22:34.222
- What are you talking about?
- The news said

22:34.265 --> 22:36.572
the police killed two members
of the Meadow in Ashville.

22:36.616 --> 22:37.878
- What?

22:37.921 --> 22:39.619
♪

22:39.662 --> 22:40.968
They killed Ray?

22:41.011 --> 22:43.100
- Calm the hell down.
- Oh, my God.

22:43.144 --> 22:44.972
It's all falling apart!
- Nothing's falling apart.

22:45.015 --> 22:46.713
Look at me.
I feel your pain about Ray.

22:46.756 --> 22:49.977
But when we get to the Seer,
everything's gonna be okay.

22:50.020 --> 22:52.501
You'll see.
Now come on, Daddy!

22:52.545 --> 22:55.199
Give us the numbers, or we're
gonna blow Mommy's brains out.

22:55.243 --> 22:57.027
- Oh, for God's sake, Mark,
just give it to them!

22:57.071 --> 22:58.551
These people have already
killed a mother

22:58.594 --> 22:59.682
and her three kids.

22:59.726 --> 23:01.162
- Lynne,
tape her damn mouth shut.

23:01.205 --> 23:03.469
- Rose is dead?
- Do what you're told!

23:03.512 --> 23:07.211
- Rose and the kids--
you killed them?

23:07.255 --> 23:09.605
Why would you do that?
[gunshots]

23:09.649 --> 23:11.346
[shrieks]

23:11.390 --> 23:14.436
[heavy breathing]

23:14.480 --> 23:17.570
[siren blares]

23:17.613 --> 23:19.441
- [sighs]

23:19.485 --> 23:22.226
♪

23:22.270 --> 23:24.577
Let's go!
Move it!

23:27.536 --> 23:29.930
- By the time we rolled up,
they were gone.

23:29.973 --> 23:31.235
We set up checkpoints,

23:31.279 --> 23:33.499
but these mountains
are riddled with back roads.

23:36.327 --> 23:39.113
- Mrs. Anderson,
I'm Agent LaCroix.

23:39.156 --> 23:41.420
Captain Parsons tells us
that you and your husband

23:41.463 --> 23:42.856
have been through
quite an ordeal.

23:42.899 --> 23:44.988
- My daughter Maya threatened
to kill us.

23:45.032 --> 23:47.774
- Was it just your daughter
and this man, Quentin Garvey?

23:47.817 --> 23:49.950
- No, there was
another young woman.

23:49.993 --> 23:52.605
She looked
absolutely terrified.

23:52.648 --> 23:55.216
That man kept yelling at her.

23:55.259 --> 23:58.437
And when Maya found out about
the people killed in Ashville,

23:58.480 --> 24:02.049
she started screaming and that
man tried to calm her down.

24:02.092 --> 24:04.181
- How?
What did he say?

24:04.225 --> 24:07.315
- Something about
meeting a Seer.

24:07.358 --> 24:10.840
Maya has been troubled before,

24:10.884 --> 24:14.061
but what this place
has done to her...

24:14.104 --> 24:15.889
- What do you mean
she was troubled?

24:15.932 --> 24:18.500
- She was molested
by a relative,

24:18.544 --> 24:21.503
and she blamed us
for not protecting her.

24:21.547 --> 24:24.375
[dramatic music]

24:24.419 --> 24:26.465
- Garvey was so focused
on the 20 grand in the safe

24:26.508 --> 24:27.901
that he overlooked
the three grand

24:27.944 --> 24:29.511
in the Andersons' wallets.

24:29.555 --> 24:31.078
- Not to mention
the major bling-age

24:31.121 --> 24:33.428
up in the master bedroom.

24:33.472 --> 24:35.474
- He'll still be on the hunt
for money.

24:35.517 --> 24:42.481
♪

24:48.574 --> 24:50.837
- That jacket looks sick
on you.

24:50.880 --> 24:53.492
- You think so?
- Oh, yeah, dude.

24:53.535 --> 24:54.884
I love your style.

24:54.928 --> 24:56.582
[both chuckle]

24:56.625 --> 24:58.932
You know what'd look so cool
with that?

24:58.975 --> 25:01.151
Some red berry lip gloss.

25:01.195 --> 25:03.066
[dark music]

25:03.110 --> 25:04.764
- I don't have any with me.

25:04.807 --> 25:06.940
♪

25:06.983 --> 25:09.116
- Here, try mine.

25:09.159 --> 25:10.552
It's new.

25:10.596 --> 25:17.516
♪

25:19.648 --> 25:21.781
- Tastes kinda funny.

25:21.824 --> 25:24.784
- Vitamin E.
Good for your skin.

25:24.827 --> 25:27.177
- Hmm.

25:29.049 --> 25:32.139
The red one.
That's my car.

25:32.182 --> 25:34.315
- You don't look so good, Cara.

25:34.358 --> 25:37.492
I should drive you home.

25:37.536 --> 25:41.583
Hey, this is my dad
and my sister.

25:41.627 --> 25:43.019
This is Cara.

25:43.063 --> 25:47.371
We have to drive her home.
- Get in.

25:52.638 --> 25:56.293
Good job, baby.
- Thanks, Dad.

25:56.337 --> 25:58.208
[engine starts]

26:06.173 --> 26:08.262
- Hey, I just got a hit
on Daisy Anderson

26:08.305 --> 26:10.177
at an ATM two hours ago
in Danville.

26:10.220 --> 26:11.613
Coming at you.

26:14.311 --> 26:15.486
- Who's the girl?

26:15.530 --> 26:17.401
She looks like
she's been drugged.

26:17.445 --> 26:19.490
- Cara Jarvis, 16,
from Alexandria.

26:19.534 --> 26:21.667
Reported missing
along with her car.

26:21.710 --> 26:23.451
- They took a grand
out of her checking account

26:23.494 --> 26:25.018
and another grand
from her credit card.

26:25.061 --> 26:26.410
- Better keep the cards active.

26:26.454 --> 26:28.630
They'll keep Cara alive
as long as she's useful.

26:28.674 --> 26:30.763
- I'm not sure
it's about the money.

26:30.806 --> 26:34.984
Pretty, rich, 16--smack in the
middle of Quentin's sweet spot.

26:35.028 --> 26:37.030
- Another bride
for the prophet?

26:37.073 --> 26:39.206
- Or maybe for the Seer.

26:39.249 --> 26:41.251
He told Daisy
they were gonna meet him.

26:41.295 --> 26:43.253
- Along with Elvis
and the Easter Bunny.

26:43.297 --> 26:45.386
- "Free minds, free hearts."

26:45.429 --> 26:48.389
[tense music]

26:48.432 --> 26:50.565
- The painter, M.W.,
he's our Seer?

26:50.609 --> 26:52.436
Well, I doubt we'll find
his work in the Met.

26:52.480 --> 26:54.438
- This is more like folk art.

26:54.482 --> 26:55.962
Painted on butcher paper

26:56.005 --> 26:59.269
with what looks like colored
pencils dipped in water.

26:59.313 --> 27:00.967
- Something I might
pull together for Anais

27:01.010 --> 27:02.316
on a snow day.

27:02.359 --> 27:04.100
- Or what an inmate
can get his hands on.

27:04.144 --> 27:06.059
- A lot of artists
spent time in prison.

27:06.102 --> 27:09.497
Garvey's cellmate,
Marcus Wilson, M.W.

27:09.540 --> 27:11.281
Shared a cell with Garvey
for three years

27:11.325 --> 27:12.674
at Central Prison in Raleigh.

27:12.718 --> 27:15.285
Charged with abduction
and rape of a minor,

27:15.329 --> 27:17.505
scheduled for release
a month from now.

27:17.548 --> 27:20.377
- Cara Jarvis could be
his get-out-of-jail present.

27:20.421 --> 27:22.075
- Not if we can help it.

27:22.118 --> 27:24.164
♪

27:30.126 --> 27:31.301
- Wilson's a Level Three
sex offender.

27:31.345 --> 27:33.129
He's at the end
of a 12-year bid.

27:33.173 --> 27:35.784
He's had plenty of time
to hone his artistic skills.

27:35.828 --> 27:37.177
- Well, is this one of his?

27:37.220 --> 27:39.614
- Oh, yeah.
He started painting boats

27:39.658 --> 27:42.530
after we confiscated his
sketches of underage girls.

27:42.573 --> 27:45.707
We didn't want to encourage
an unhealthy obsession.

27:45.751 --> 27:47.361
This is one
of his earlier works.

27:47.404 --> 27:48.667
- How can you tell?

27:48.710 --> 27:50.712
- Butcher paper,
watercolor paint,

27:50.756 --> 27:53.367
now he can afford canvas,
oil paints.

27:53.410 --> 27:54.847
- Is someone buying
his paintings?

27:54.890 --> 27:56.196
- [sighs]
Lord no.

27:56.239 --> 27:58.720
Wilson's had a $1,000
coming into his account

27:58.764 --> 28:00.679
every month
for the last five years.

28:00.722 --> 28:03.333
It's made his time
in here pretty easy.

28:04.508 --> 28:05.945
- Five years ago.

28:05.988 --> 28:07.860
Right when Garvey got
the Meadow up and running.

28:07.903 --> 28:10.863
[eerie music]

28:10.906 --> 28:12.386
♪

28:12.429 --> 28:14.736
- Quintin hung on to this?

28:14.780 --> 28:17.739
I'm flattered.
- Why boats?

28:17.783 --> 28:19.872
- I grew up by the ocean
in Cape May.

28:19.915 --> 28:21.308
- "Free minds, free hearts."

28:21.351 --> 28:22.744
That come from
your childhood too?

28:22.788 --> 28:24.224
- It's my own thinking.

28:24.267 --> 28:27.401
Cleanse yourself of the evils
of modern technology.

28:27.444 --> 28:30.230
Free your mind
and find the power of love.

28:30.273 --> 28:33.015
- The gospel according
to Quentin Garvey.

28:33.059 --> 28:35.061
- He was curious.
I educated him.

28:35.104 --> 28:36.497
- You gave him an angle,

28:36.540 --> 28:39.108
and he pays you back
with canteen money.

28:39.152 --> 28:41.807
You also share an interest
in teenage girls.

28:41.850 --> 28:44.505
- All my partners
gave me consent.

28:44.548 --> 28:46.420
- After you roofied
and raped them.

28:46.463 --> 28:48.814
♪

28:48.857 --> 28:50.598
- We're not here to argue,
Mr. Wilson.

28:50.641 --> 28:53.819
We need help finding Garvey.
Maybe he reached out to you.

28:55.646 --> 28:57.997
We can help with your parole.

28:58.040 --> 28:59.781
- I don't need your help.

28:59.825 --> 29:01.435
I've been a good boy in here.

29:01.478 --> 29:03.393
After they calculate
my good time,

29:03.437 --> 29:05.091
I'll be out of here
yesterday.

29:05.134 --> 29:07.310
My plan is to find a lady...

29:07.354 --> 29:08.921
♪

29:08.964 --> 29:12.141
My own age and settle down.

29:12.185 --> 29:16.189
As for old Quentin,
good luck and good riddance.

29:16.232 --> 29:17.712
- He's gonna need luck,

29:17.756 --> 29:20.019
with three girls on his hands
and nowhere to run.

29:20.062 --> 29:26.634
♪

29:26.677 --> 29:28.854
- His problems
aren't my burden.

29:30.681 --> 29:32.466
Guard.

29:32.509 --> 29:34.903
- Cop interview three!

29:34.947 --> 29:37.253
[door buzzing]

29:41.997 --> 29:44.826
- You see his eyes light up
at the mention

29:44.870 --> 29:46.610
of Garvey's
travelling companions?

29:46.654 --> 29:48.961
- I've never seen eyes drool.

29:49.004 --> 29:50.658
- As soon as he gets
a release date,

29:50.701 --> 29:51.964
he'll reach out to Garvey.

29:52.007 --> 29:53.443
- You really wanna
wait a month?

29:53.487 --> 29:55.358
- Warden, how much time off
will Wilson get

29:55.402 --> 29:56.707
for good behavior?

29:56.751 --> 29:59.928
- I wanna max this guy out.
No early release.

29:59.972 --> 30:01.495
- Warden, we're not
actually asking you

30:01.538 --> 30:04.585
to give him time off,
but we'd like Wilson to think

30:04.628 --> 30:06.065
he was getting out tomorrow.

30:06.108 --> 30:08.719
- Run a game on Wilson?

30:08.763 --> 30:10.983
- If we're right, and
he does reach out to Garvey,

30:11.026 --> 30:13.246
he'll get another five years
for aiding and abetting.

30:15.639 --> 30:19.121
- The map will post
on their website tomorrow.

30:19.165 --> 30:23.169
So, uh, take a look
and let me know what you think.

30:23.212 --> 30:24.866
Okay?

30:24.910 --> 30:27.738
Night, sweetie.
Love you.

30:27.782 --> 30:30.045
- Treasure map?

30:30.089 --> 30:32.352
- Orienteering competition.
[sighs]

30:32.395 --> 30:34.920
Tali used to do it
with Angelyne all the time.

30:34.963 --> 30:36.356
She loved it.

30:36.399 --> 30:37.792
I'm trying
to get her interested

30:37.836 --> 30:41.100
in doing one with me, but
I'm not having much success.

30:41.143 --> 30:43.754
- Life goes on.

30:43.798 --> 30:45.887
Tough lesson to learn.

30:47.933 --> 30:49.891
You sure you charged
that Stingray?

30:49.935 --> 30:51.545
- Yeah, it's working.

30:51.588 --> 30:54.026
If anyone uses a burner in that
prison, we'll know about it.

30:54.069 --> 30:56.028
- He's probably been waiting
for this moment

30:56.071 --> 30:57.464
ever since Quentin
got out of jail

30:57.507 --> 30:59.379
and started luring young women
to the Meadow.

30:59.422 --> 31:01.598
[buzzing]
- We got a hit.

31:02.382 --> 31:05.907
It's an encrypted DM posted
to a hockey message board.

31:05.951 --> 31:07.996
Old tech.
Easy to unscramble.

31:08.040 --> 31:09.780
"Out in two days,

31:09.824 --> 31:11.739
"can solve your problem
if you bring treats.

31:11.782 --> 31:13.219
Interested?"

31:13.262 --> 31:15.308
- And there's a reply
from one of Garvey's burners.

31:15.351 --> 31:16.613
- Definitely.

31:16.657 --> 31:18.746
- And Wilson just wrote back
and disconnected.

31:18.789 --> 31:20.922
- Meet me at the blue boat.

31:20.966 --> 31:24.012
- Boats.
Cape May where Wilson grew up.

31:24.708 --> 31:27.624
- Maybe a way out
of the country by boat.

31:27.668 --> 31:29.191
Two marinas in Cape May.

31:29.235 --> 31:31.324
- Two teams.
We need to cover both.

31:31.367 --> 31:33.935
- Call the warden, make sure
she puts Wilson in isolation.

31:33.979 --> 31:36.068
♪

31:36.111 --> 31:39.071
[ominous music]

31:39.114 --> 31:42.030
♪

31:42.074 --> 31:43.553
- Cara, listen to me.

31:43.597 --> 31:46.905
Tell Quentin and Daisy
that something's wrong with me.

31:46.948 --> 31:48.819
- Why?
What are you gonna do?

31:48.863 --> 31:50.691
- When they come in here,
run.

31:50.734 --> 31:52.954
- But what about you?

31:52.998 --> 31:56.001
- [coughing]
Go!

31:56.827 --> 31:58.481
- It's Leanne.

31:58.525 --> 32:00.570
Something's really wrong
with her.

32:02.572 --> 32:04.923
♪

32:04.966 --> 32:06.707
- Hey!

32:10.537 --> 32:12.452
- Get up.
[grunts]

32:12.495 --> 32:13.670
- [cries]

32:13.714 --> 32:15.672
- Now you have something
to moan about.

32:15.716 --> 32:18.632
[suspenseful music]

32:18.675 --> 32:25.639
♪

32:26.901 --> 32:28.468
- I thought they'd let me go

32:28.511 --> 32:30.992
after they couldn't get
any more money out of me,

32:31.036 --> 32:32.559
but I was wrong.

32:32.602 --> 32:34.691
Leanne told me
Quentin is a perv,

32:34.735 --> 32:37.651
and he's gonna force her
to marry him.

32:37.694 --> 32:39.958
It's because of her
I was able to run away.

32:40.001 --> 32:42.003
- Any idea
where they're heading?

32:42.047 --> 32:44.266
- We were in
North Carolina yesterday

32:44.310 --> 32:46.181
when Quentin got
some kind of message,

32:46.225 --> 32:47.922
and we started driving south.

32:47.966 --> 32:50.055
- Did you make any stops?

32:50.098 --> 32:51.882
- For gas.

32:51.926 --> 32:53.275
And a Home Depot.

32:53.319 --> 32:56.887
Daisy went in and bought
a generator and a gas can.

32:56.931 --> 32:58.367
I don't know what for.

32:58.411 --> 33:01.457
- Her parents just arrived
at the state police barracks.

33:01.501 --> 33:04.025
- Can I see them?
Please?

33:04.069 --> 33:06.158
- Of course.

33:09.422 --> 33:10.771
- Ma'am, watch your step.

33:10.814 --> 33:12.033
- It's not Cape May.

33:12.077 --> 33:14.079
Quentin wouldn't need
a generator

33:14.122 --> 33:15.819
if he was getting on a boat.

33:15.863 --> 33:18.518
- The Blue Boat's a place.
- Maybe a bar.

33:19.258 --> 33:20.737
- Don't jump to easy answers.

33:20.781 --> 33:23.044
I did with Cape May,
and it cost us time.

33:23.088 --> 33:26.395
♪

33:31.487 --> 33:32.793
- Got a Blue Boat cruise
in Amsterdam

33:32.836 --> 33:34.273
and a Blue Boat restaurant.

33:34.316 --> 33:36.405
- I've got "The Blue Boat" by
Winslow Homer

33:36.449 --> 33:38.451
at the Museum of
Fine Arts in Boston.

33:38.494 --> 33:40.931
- I've got a dozen Blue Boat
paintings by different artists.

33:40.975 --> 33:42.455
Popular subject.

33:42.498 --> 33:44.065
- Yeah, but why would
a predator

33:44.109 --> 33:46.328
like Marcus Wilson paint one?

33:46.372 --> 33:47.721
They took away his paintings,

33:47.764 --> 33:49.897
paintings of young girls
that aroused him

33:49.940 --> 33:53.466
and brought back
memories of sexual assaults.

33:53.509 --> 33:55.033
[investigative music]

33:55.076 --> 33:56.208
So...

33:56.251 --> 33:58.732
♪

33:58.775 --> 34:01.039
So instead he started
painting boats?

34:01.082 --> 34:02.779
Maybe the painting
triggered him.

34:02.823 --> 34:04.781
Maybe it turned him on

34:04.825 --> 34:06.957
and reminded him
of one of his victims.

34:07.001 --> 34:08.611
- Maybe the place
where he assaulted her.

34:08.655 --> 34:10.135
- I'm on it.

34:11.875 --> 34:13.660
First arrest in 1991.

34:13.703 --> 34:15.444
Sexual assault
in Clayton, Georgia.

34:15.488 --> 34:17.272
Victim, 14-year-old girl.

34:17.316 --> 34:19.492
Wilson was a counselor
at a summer camp.

34:19.535 --> 34:21.320
- The Burton Lake Camp.

34:22.886 --> 34:24.236
- Got it here!

34:24.279 --> 34:27.543
Burton Lake Camp--canoe trips,
woodcrafts, sailing.

34:27.587 --> 34:30.981
Closed ten years ago,
but look at this.

34:31.025 --> 34:32.287
The Blue Boat.

34:32.331 --> 34:34.246
- Satellite photo?
- Right here.

34:35.203 --> 34:37.162
Photo was taken two years ago.

34:37.858 --> 34:39.120
Camp's still there.

34:39.164 --> 34:43.342
♪

34:46.432 --> 34:49.609
[all breathing heavily]

34:50.871 --> 34:52.438
- Hold.

34:52.481 --> 34:55.397
[tense music]

34:55.441 --> 34:59.488
♪

34:59.532 --> 35:01.055
- I've got three
heat signatures.

35:01.099 --> 35:04.102
- I'm seeing two cell signals
coming from that building.

35:04.145 --> 35:06.147
- Go on.

35:06.191 --> 35:11.021
♪

35:11.065 --> 35:14.590
[phone ringing]

35:23.121 --> 35:27.037
- Quentin Garvey, this is
Agent Jess LaCroix of the FBI.

35:27.081 --> 35:28.865
We have you surrounded.

35:28.909 --> 35:31.738
I'd like to work out a way to
get you out of there safely.

35:31.781 --> 35:33.696
Are you listening to me,
Mr. Garvey?

35:33.740 --> 35:36.743
- Call the Meadow.
Tell Iris it's Omega.

35:36.786 --> 35:39.485
♪

35:39.528 --> 35:41.574
- I can hear you.
- Good.

35:41.617 --> 35:43.489
Now there's an easy way
to do this.

35:43.532 --> 35:45.230
You come out of there
one by one

35:45.273 --> 35:46.535
with your hands
above your head.

35:46.579 --> 35:48.798
- That's not gonna work for me.

35:48.842 --> 35:51.497
This is how this is gonna go:
Iris can you hear me?

35:51.540 --> 35:53.368
- I do, Quentin.

35:53.412 --> 35:57.111
- Agent LaCroix, I have
an open line to the Meadow.

35:57.155 --> 35:59.505
Everyone there
is gathering for Omega.

35:59.548 --> 36:01.202
- Don't do it, Mr. Garvey.

36:01.246 --> 36:02.856
- It's our suicide covenant.

36:02.899 --> 36:05.728
If you move on us or the Meadow
or if you try jam this call,

36:05.772 --> 36:08.166
everyone there will be dead
within 20 minutes.

36:08.209 --> 36:11.386
If you push us, we are prepared
to die for our freedom.

36:11.430 --> 36:14.346
Free minds, free hearts.

36:14.389 --> 36:16.261
♪

36:16.304 --> 36:18.263
- All right, Mr. Garvey,
I'm listening.

36:18.306 --> 36:20.395
Talk to me.
What's the way out?

36:20.439 --> 36:22.615
- Safe passage to a place
of my choosing

36:22.658 --> 36:24.356
for me and my two companions.

36:24.399 --> 36:26.314
- I can make that happen.

36:26.358 --> 36:28.360
But first I need
a show of good faith from you.

36:28.403 --> 36:30.927
I need to come inside,
see Daisy, Leanne,

36:30.971 --> 36:32.364
make sure they're okay.

36:33.365 --> 36:34.931
- I'm not letting you in.

36:34.975 --> 36:37.020
- It's non-negotiable,
Mr. Garvey.

36:37.064 --> 36:38.892
You refuse,
we'll wait you out.

36:38.935 --> 36:41.590
Gets cold out here at night.
Your generator's not set up.

36:41.634 --> 36:44.158
You have no heating,
no electricity.

36:44.202 --> 36:45.507
You'll run out of food.

36:45.551 --> 36:47.683
It'll get pretty miserable
pretty quick.

36:49.468 --> 36:51.383
But if you let me in,

36:51.426 --> 36:54.908
you'll be on your way,
wherever you want.

36:56.344 --> 36:58.564
- Okay.

36:58.607 --> 37:02.437
But not tricks
or everybody dies.

37:03.830 --> 37:05.484
[sighs]

37:05.527 --> 37:12.665
♪

37:40.345 --> 37:43.522
Okay, okay.
Far enough.

37:44.436 --> 37:46.351
Take that jacket off.

37:50.355 --> 37:52.226
- How you doing, Leanne?

37:52.270 --> 37:54.315
Those bruises on your face?
How'd you get those?

37:54.359 --> 37:55.490
- She's fine.
She fell.

37:55.534 --> 37:57.971
- I wanna hear it from her.

37:58.014 --> 38:00.756
- I'm fine.
It was an accident.

38:00.800 --> 38:03.324
- What about you, Daisy?
How're you doing?

38:03.368 --> 38:05.718
- Fine.

38:07.023 --> 38:09.069
- You came here expecting
to meet the Seer,

38:09.112 --> 38:10.549
didn't you, Daisy?

38:10.592 --> 38:12.115
Did Quentin tell you
who the Seer is?

38:12.159 --> 38:15.554
- You've spoken to the girls.
Now go get us that transport.

38:15.597 --> 38:20.080
- Helicopter's coming, I just
wanna show Daisy something.

38:22.561 --> 38:24.954
The Seer painted it.

38:24.998 --> 38:26.608
Free minds, free hearts.

38:26.652 --> 38:29.437
Put it there on the table
and leave.

38:29.481 --> 38:30.656
- That's his initials
right there.

38:30.699 --> 38:33.528
M.W.
Marcus Wilson.

38:33.572 --> 38:35.617
You wanna tell Daisy
who the Seer is?

38:35.661 --> 38:37.402
- It doesn't matter.

38:37.445 --> 38:41.928
- He's Quentin's ex-cellmate
from Central Prison in Raleigh.

38:41.971 --> 38:44.191
- The truth can come
from any man.

38:44.234 --> 38:47.325
- The truth came from a man
serving 12 years

38:47.368 --> 38:49.936
for raping underage girls.

38:49.979 --> 38:52.373
He committed one of his crimes
right here.

38:52.417 --> 38:54.419
That's why he painted
that boat.

38:54.462 --> 38:56.377
Same as the one
at the entrance.

38:56.421 --> 38:58.118
Because it reminded him.
- No, no, no.

38:58.161 --> 39:01.121
Wilson was rehabilitated.
- Not a chance.

39:01.164 --> 39:04.080
When Quentin arranged
to meet him here,

39:04.124 --> 39:06.909
Wilson agreed to help
if he brought him treats.

39:06.953 --> 39:09.695
Treats, Daisy.
Young girls like you were.

39:09.738 --> 39:11.261
He brought you here

39:11.305 --> 39:13.394
to put you together
with this child rapist.

39:13.438 --> 39:14.569
The same as the man
who hurt you.

39:14.613 --> 39:17.442
- Shut up!
- Free minds, free hearts!

39:17.485 --> 39:18.617
He came up with that.

39:18.660 --> 39:21.141
The Meadow came out
of his head.

39:21.184 --> 39:23.056
It's his fantasy.

39:23.099 --> 39:24.927
Quentin just convinced you
to live in it.

39:24.971 --> 39:27.539
He scammed you for your body
and for your money.

39:27.582 --> 39:33.632
♪

39:33.675 --> 39:36.417
- Hey, no, no, no.
No, Daisy, no.

39:36.461 --> 39:38.071
- You're just like them.

39:38.767 --> 39:40.290
You're like all of them.

39:40.334 --> 39:43.250
- Don't listen to this man.
He's lying to you.

39:43.293 --> 39:44.817
- Daisy.

39:45.774 --> 39:47.602
Come toward me, Daisy.

39:47.646 --> 39:50.562
He's not worth it.
Just come towards me.

39:52.477 --> 39:54.957
That's it.
Keep coming.

39:55.001 --> 39:57.612
That's it.
I gotcha.

39:58.874 --> 40:01.834
I gotcha, I gotcha.
- [cries]

40:01.877 --> 40:03.531
- Okay, now I want you
to go out the door.

40:03.575 --> 40:05.881
I promise, you'll be safe.

40:05.925 --> 40:09.058
Go, go, go.

40:11.713 --> 40:14.803
Now, Leanne,
I want you to be brave.

40:14.847 --> 40:16.762
Your sister Nellie
is still alive.

40:16.805 --> 40:18.503
- Oh, my God.
[crying]

40:18.546 --> 40:20.418
- Son of a bitch.

40:20.461 --> 40:23.203
- Now when I say go, I want you
to do everything you can

40:23.246 --> 40:25.205
to break free of Quentin.
Understand?

40:25.248 --> 40:27.903
- You so much as move,
and I will kill you.

40:27.947 --> 40:30.602
- He won't shoot you.

40:32.081 --> 40:35.607
- Iris!
Are you ready for Omega?

40:35.650 --> 40:37.565
- He's a scammer.

40:37.609 --> 40:39.480
- Iris!

40:39.524 --> 40:42.048
- He cons other people
into doing his killing for him.

40:42.091 --> 40:45.399
- Iris!
- I can't...

40:45.443 --> 40:47.096
I won't do it, Quentin!

40:47.140 --> 40:49.534
- He's probably never fired
a shot in his life.

40:49.577 --> 40:51.710
- No, no, no.
You just try me.

40:51.753 --> 40:53.973
- Even forgot to take
the safety off his gun.

40:54.016 --> 40:55.409
- Don't you believe it.
- Go!

40:55.453 --> 40:56.932
- [grunts]
- Aah!

40:57.455 --> 40:58.934
[gunshot]

40:58.978 --> 41:02.111
[uplifting music]

41:02.155 --> 41:04.810
♪

41:04.853 --> 41:07.769
- [heavy breathing]

41:07.813 --> 41:13.558
♪

41:13.601 --> 41:15.995
- All clear.
We're coming out.

41:19.781 --> 41:21.740
[indistinct radio chatter]

41:21.783 --> 41:23.393
- Hold for Leanne.

41:23.437 --> 41:27.920
- Oh, my God, Nellie?
Is that really you?

41:27.963 --> 41:29.965
- So was the safety on or off?

41:30.009 --> 41:32.490
- I don't know.
Couldn't tell.

41:32.533 --> 41:34.535
[police chatter]

41:34.579 --> 41:36.668
- Where are you?

41:36.711 --> 41:39.758
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

41:39.801 --> 41:43.457
I just can't believe
you're alive.

41:43.501 --> 41:45.633
♪

41:45.677 --> 41:48.680
[indistinct radio chatter]

41:48.723 --> 41:52.814
♪

41:52.858 --> 41:55.338
- There it is!

41:58.646 --> 42:00.996
- There you go.

42:01.736 --> 42:05.131
- Punched.
- Okay, where to next?

42:05.174 --> 42:07.699
I'm really glad you decided
to do this with me.

42:07.742 --> 42:09.265
- Well, it's what you texted.

42:09.309 --> 42:12.007
Mom would still want me to do
things that I liked.

42:12.051 --> 42:14.270
- Yeah, she would,
and it would break my heart

42:14.314 --> 42:15.968
for you to give up things
